Governors of the 36 States of the federation under the aegis of the Nigerian Governors’ Forum (NGF) yesterday met to discuss a new approach to tackle the raging security challenges across the country. The first inaugural meeting to be chaired by Governor Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti State was held at NGF Secretariat in Abuja ahead of today’s National Economic Council (NEC), Nigeria’s apex economic advisory body being presided over by Vice President Yemi Osinbajo. The meeting, according to the agenda, reviewed ‘Feedback on Governors’ Meeting with Mr President on Security Review of NEC. The focus on the security was to fashion out a more pragmatic approach to secure the country in the midst of various security challenges. The meeting, going by the agenda, considered the guidelines issued by the Nigerian Financial Intelligence Unit (NFIU) preventing the governors from accessing funds meant for local governments. Other issues listed for discussion yesterday included the planned one Day Workshop on World Bank’s Engagement with States; one Day IGR Retreat for Governors and Chairmen of State Boards of Internal Revenue. There was also the presentation of a book on Sub-National Investment Promotion by Ms. Yewande Sadiku, Executive Secretary/CEO, Nigerian Investment Promotion Commission (NIPC). Governors’ meet ahead of NEC meeting Fayemi at NGF: The call to duty Osinbajo, governors raise alarm over population explosion, ‘tiny’ economy Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin